**Temporary Workaround for curators**

1. Remove the mod from the collection.
2. Uninstall the affected mod completely (DO NOT use the re-install functionality as that forwards the installer options)
3. Install the mod, selecting the wanted options.
3. Close Vortex
4. Start Vortex and add the mod to the collection.
5. Publish a new revision.

**Users**
The mods that are part of the collection are still installed correctly even though the collection UI is stating that the collection is incomplete - ignore the collection UI and verify the mod installations within the mods page instead.

**Describe the bug**
When a collection is created and includes a mod file with the update policy of "Prefer Exact" it will attempt to use the same file unless it is archived or deleted. If the file is archived, Vortex will take the latest version of that file. However, in the situation it appears to not apply any rules intended for the old version of the mod to the new version.

A workaround for curators is to use the "Exact only" update policy, but this will break if the mod is permanently removed and requires a new revision to be added for each mod update. 

