**Describe the bug**
When downloading BepInEx from Github using the built-in bepinex extension, I receive an invalid installer error as shown below. There does not seem to be any issue with the downloaded files, just the error itself. This is forcing Github download of the IL2CPP version of BepInEx.

**To Reproduce**
Steps to reproduce the behavior:
1. Start managing a Unity game that downloads the IL2CPP version of BepInEx from Github.
2. See the error.

**Expected behavior**
No error when built-in bepinex extension installs from Github

This is the code that was used, for reference:

```
context.once(() => {
    //Download BepinEx and register with extension
    if (context.api.ext.bepinexAddGame !== undefined) {
      context.api.ext.bepinexAddGame({
        gameId: GAME_ID,
        autoDownloadBepInEx: true,
        architecture: 'x64', // <--- This will download version for 64-bit games
        forceGithubDownload: true, // <--- This will force Vortex to download directly from Github
        unityBuild: 'unityil2cpp', // <--- This will default to version 6.0.0 of BepInEx that supports IL2CPP
      });
    }
  });
```

